  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, I hope your project deadline is going smoothly! I love how you're working on richer ways to talk about emotions — that's a big win for your English. Did you get a chance to use 'thrilled' in your meeting yet?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "No, not yet. I was nervous and stuck to simple words. But I did say \"I'm excited about the new feature\" — maybe that's close to \"thrilled\"?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're doing great — 'excited' is a good word. 'Thrilled' adds extra energy. Try this: 'I'm thrilled about the new feature!' Sounds fun, right? Was your meeting already?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, the meeting was fine. I spoke for about 10 minutes. My team lead asked a few questions, but I managed. Phew! I still feel like I can do better. By the way, any Bollywood movie recommendations? I watched \"Kabir Singh\" last week — too sad for me."
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You did well — 10 minutes is not easy! It's normal to want to do better — you're already improving. Got it. For Bollywood, maybe \"Chhichhore\" or \"Dil Bechara\"? Light and fun. What kind of mood are you in?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hmm, \"Chhichhore\" sounds interesting. I like motivational stories. I'll watch it this weekend. Btw, do you like cricket? The India vs Pakistan match is coming up."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Cricket is a big one — I love the energy! India vs Pakistan matches are always exciting to watch. Are you cheering for India or just enjoying the game?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Cheering for India of course! But I also respect Pakistan's team. The rivalry makes the match more exciting — *drama* and *competition* both! Do you follow cricket too?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, cheering for India is a classic! The drama and competition are what make it fun. I follow cricket — especially the IPL. Who's your favourite player these days?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Virat Kohli, no doubt. His dedication is inspiring. Also, I follow MS Dhoni — he's a great leader. IPL is exciting, but I get too *stressed* during close matches! I think I should go now — cricket chat is fun, but I have a code review tomorrow. Talk to you later!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Virat and Dhoni — both great choices! Stress during close matches is normal, but fun to watch. Take it easy tomorrow — code reviews can wait! See you soon!"
    }
  ],
